	<description><![CDATA[This mambot provides the same functionality as the scrolling images mambot from the expose guys, as a mambot. <br />
The syntax is {expose}GalleryId,GalleryWidth,Speed{/expose} where GalleryId is the ID of the gallery you want to use, GalleryWidth is the 
width in pixels, and Speed is the speed. For speed, smaller is faster with 1 being the fastest<br />
<br />
Demonstration of the expose scroller mambot tag: {expose}6,600px,25{/expose}<br />
<br />
<b>note:</b> If you don't follow this rigorous structure, the mambot will not work. Anyone wanting to help with the regex 
for this application is welcome to e-mail me to make it a little more flexible!<br />
<br />
This mambot was developed by <a href="http://www.jamesguthrie.ch">James Guthrie</a> for his useage <br />
Please send feedback to scroller[at]jamesguthrie[dot]ch <br />
<br />
<b>Please note!</b> As this creation is a "hack" of the existing module for a specific purpose it is
more than likely that you will have to mess around in the expose.php file to change parameters, or that large
areas of how it is done are really dodgy. But it works for me!<br />
If you'd like to suggest changes then send me an e-mail, I'd be more than willing to check it out.<br />
<br />
Also, I realise that there is the possibility to include paramers in the module settings in the backend but
as I don't need that functionality it's not present. If you're reading this you can probably figure it out on
your own, otherwise if you send me an e-mail I might be able to check it out.<br />
<br />
James.]]></description>
